    <stitle>DT 466 / DT 570 / HT 570 Service Manual - 2004 Emissions with EGR - Cylinder Head and Valve Train -
        Reconditioning - Installing Valves
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="2">
        <title>Installing Valves</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Cleaning</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Clean the valve faces and seats with a suitable cleaning solvent. Dry all components
                    using filtered
                    <hotlnk xrefid="safety10" appearance="hottext">compressed air</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To clean valve guides, coat a brush with soap and water. Insert the brush into each
                    valve guide bore and rotate in one direction with an up and down motion. Dry the valve guide bores
                    using filtered
                    <hotlnk xrefid="safety10" appearance="hottext">compressed air</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insert a large nylon brush in the rear of the fuel rail gallery to loosen any dirt and
                    deposits. Blow out any debris using filtered
                    <hotlnk xrefid="safety10" appearance="hottext">compressed air</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Assembly</title>
            <figure id="f2650556" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figH08/H08002.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Installing valve stem seal, spring, and valve rotator</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Valve rotator</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Valve spring</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Valve stem</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Valve stem seal</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lubricate the valve stems with clean engine oil and insert into the valve guides.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lubricate the inside diameter of the new valve stem seals with clean engine oil. Install
                    the seals over the valve stems and valve guides. Make sure that the seals are completely seated
                    against the cylinder head spring pockets.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the valve springs over the valve stem seals.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Then install the valve rotators on top of the valve springs.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid serious personal injury or possible death, wear safety glasses before using the valve
                        spring compressor.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f2650557" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figH08/H08016.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Installing valve spring retainer keys</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Valve spring compressor tool</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Valve spring retainer key</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install a valve spring compressor tool over the valve, see
                    <hotlnk document="eges2651_108.xml" xrefid="t2650505">cylinder head and valve special service
                        tools</hotlnk>. Compress the valve spring.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the valve spring retainer keys.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
